simpleText:
Ram Temple: Will it boost India's soft power?
 Leave a comment and let us know your thoughts
author: @Firstpost

simpleText: Banking on a temple to boost India's soft power, even the need of discussing it in social media is not very promising for India's future. Religion has to be a personal choice. We don't want religion to be a factor to assert our power anywhere. Rather individuals should assert their power on their individual capabilities , talents and efforts. The same goes for the country. Sriram is always here, with or without the temple. If we can only feel his presence by a temple being built in Ayodhya, then all of us need to go back and study Ramayanam again and this time learn it the right way. Building this temple after all the tragic events that occured in past several hundred years, is historic and is a reason to rejoice for all those who has been waiting for this. Please leave it at that and don't connect it to the country's power.
author: @malinisarovar

simpleText: It's as clear as daylight that the temple is a result of pure vote bank politics. Everything about this temple has been bloodied by our citizens despite their religious orientation.  Is it really worth it ? A national holiday for the central government employees just to attend the Pooja ? All the media attention about the PM being the chief guest isn't it a paid gimmick for the upcoming elections ? Isn't there somewhere we are losing the soul of our constitution that's routed in secularism, equality and unity rooted in diversity ? I guess these are some of the questions  the media should raise.

simpleText: He is not prophet dear. He is God Himself. The avatar of the Supreme Divine of the cosmos and time. The Supreme deity of Creation and Destruction. The One and Only but with many names and many forms.  When He exhales, thousands of universes emerges and one "Brahma" is born in each universe. When Mahavishnu inhales, all universes get sucked and Brahma dies.  The Lord of finite to infinite. The lord of the smallest of things, living and non-living to the largest and greatest of seas of universes.   Bhagavad Gita describes this form of Vishnu: Has 3 forms.  The first, Mahā Viṣhṇu, creates the total material energy, known as the mahat-tattva. The second, Garbhodakaśāyī Viṣṇu, enters into all the universes to create diversities and the third, Kṣīrodakaśāyī Vishnu, is diffused as the all-pervading super soul in all the universes; in the heart of every living being, is known as Paramātmā. He is present even within the atoms.The goal of life is to know the Supreme Divine, who is situated within the heart of every living being as Paramātmā, the four-handed Viṣṇu form.

simpleText:
Why are Muslims trying to be oppressive all over the world?  Why do they want to destroy other religions and replace them with their own?  Why are they so keen to build their religious monuments and mosques in locations where other religious worshipping places already exist?  
 
 The Muslims have so much land in India, and the government allows them to build mosques wherever they want.  But they only want to take over the places where the majority of Hindus congregate to pray or worship. They could build any number of Islamic mosques in any other part of India. But their bone of contention is Ayodhya because a Muslim invader known as Babur built a mosque in Ayodhya, forgetting long before Babur set foot in India, Ayodhya did exist and was believed to be the capital of Prince Rama's kingdom. 
 
  Granted Prince Rama came to be regarded as a deity in later years, we need to understand something here. The Hindu religion unlike the other world religions, does not have a founder.  It is a combination of several different teachings and philosophies with a strong element of mysticism. Accordingly, the Hindu religion has several Gods and deities, more than we could count off-hand.  Ignorant folks from alien cultures, who do not understand the deeper meaning of this would think it is merely based on foolish idol worship since there are various different Gods in the Hindu pantheon. In reality, every God is nothing more than a metaphor that symbolizes a philosophy and moral of life.  The amalgamation of all these makes up the most profound and insightful philosophy that is so deep and difficult for the comprehension, of the average human mind.  
 
 Unfortunately, Muslims in India want to build their mosques in Ayodhya. In the bygone centuries, the Islamic powers invaded India.  They not only destroyed most of the aesthetically beautiful architectural marvels of Hindu temples but also ruthlessly killed a large population of women, children, and the elderly. Anybody who submitted to their barbaric violence was forcibly converted to Islam.  By the way, I admit the caste system is the biggest crime committed in Hindu society.   The caste segregation in Hindu society is a total madness and a crime against humanity itself.  The Hindu religious base controlling the society committed this worst sin against humanity. Helpless downtrodden, ostracized people in the Hindu society, embraced Islam because Islam never discriminated against them based on the madness of the Hindu caste system. The caste system was introduced by the ones who controlled the Hindu temple-worshipping hierarchy that influenced the society in the name of God and to this day. This is a neurosis in the minds of evil people in the Hindu society in India. 
 
 Regardless, the atrocities by the Islamic invasion have been inhumanely violent to appease Allah.  Anybody who follows another religion is considered to be desecrating Islam and therefore committing blasphemy against Allah. During the Islamic invasions, the Hindu women who opposed were raped and killed while the ones who submitted in fear of life were forcibly converted to Islam. Is this something to be proud of by any community?   Look at the present-day Western countries that respect diversity. The advanced societies in the West want to see unity in diversity.  But, it is only Muslims who want to encroach into the Western way of life and build their religious relics and mosques in Western countries.  But will these same Muslims allow any other religious symbols or places of worship in the native countries they migrate from?   
 
 Why do Muslims want to destroy other cultures?  The world is for everybody. Why can't Muslims co-exist with other cultures and religions in harmony?
  Nobody knows what God really is. Humankind will never evolve to a point and develop the capacity so as to comprehend the unknown origin of all mysteries.  The concept of God is a social construct that came out of the human psyche to regulate society. But idiots talk and preach like they know all the answers to everything connected to the unknown mysteries of the origin of the universe. They make the people believe it is real and they tell them it is a personal experience. The herd of human masses is completely brainwashed. Raising questions in this regard is construed and considered blasphemy. We are told faith is the only answer.  If you believe you will find.  No, our rational minds reject this. We have to find in order to believe. 
 
  If you try to rationally educate an idiot, it proves there are two of you. Idiots are stubborn and opinionated. The first step of enlightenment is to know what you will never know. Never try to explain something to an opinionated fanatic.  If you do, you are making a fool of yourself.  Once an idea is inculcated in their mind, that becomes the truth, the whole truth, and nothing but the truth so help you God.  
 
 The humankind clouded with their own ignorance takes it way beyond human rationale. All religious sects have become nothing but lucrative commercial enterprises generating one of the greatest revenues in the world. This is systematically carried out by way of capitalizing on the fear of human ignorance.  People behind religions sell the concept of God to the masses and live comfortably and well, while the hopeless ignorant masses become the believers.  World leaders and politicians encourage this and make the religious followings their vote-banks.  
 As far as India goes, Muslim invasions began after c. 1000, establishing the long-lived Delhi sultanate in 1206 and the Mughal dynasty in 1526. Long before Babur came to India, Ayodhya existed.  But the Muslims want their mosque in Ayodhya. Why can't they find another place to build what they want?  Their religious indoctrination drives them to resort to violence and aggression paving the way to destruction and annihilation of other religions and cultures. 
 
 Any civilized society allows freedom of speech and accepts the fact that everybody ought to think freely and develop their own perceptions supported by human rationale.   The world is for everybody. Let's pray and hope that the Almighty Allah will dispel this human ignorance. Live and let live. Let's endeavor to make the world a civilized place not run by religious fanatics and lunatics.
